STATE of North Carolina
v.
Raymond Craig JOHNSON No. 431P18 Supreme Court of North Carolina. January 30, 2019 Daniel P. O'Brien, Special Deputy Attorney General, James R. O'Neill, District Attorney, for State of North Carolina. Raymond Craig Johnson, for Johnson, Raymond Craig

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 10th of December 2018 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the North Carolina Court of Appeals, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Dismissed by order of the Court in conference, this the 30th of January 2019."
